President Biden has declared a major disaster in California and authorized federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts from Tropical Storm Hilary, which occurred from August 19 to August 21, 2023. The federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures in the affected counties. Andrew F. Grant of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.